// <auto-generated>
// Rust port of the .NET scheduler server. A standalone node that fires workflows
// on a cron schedule and dispatches them to script agents.
//
//   - Binds the first free port in 5000-5100 and self-registers in
//     core.server_node as a `Scheduler` (status Online); marks itself Offline on
//     SIGINT/SIGTERM.
//   - Runs a cron thread (the Rust port of QuartzSchedulerThread): it loads every
//     active workflow whose Schedule has all cron component FKs populated,
//     assembles a standard cron expression from the parts (applying the
//     Every/Exactly modifier and Quartz dom/dow reconciliation), and fires
//     `execute(workflow_id)` when due. Schedules are reloaded every 5 minutes.
//   - `execute` (also exposed at POST /api/scheduler/execute) expands a Folder
//     workflow into its child workflows (recursively), groups them by `seq`, and
//     in seq order dispatches each Process workflow to its agent's
//     `/api/scriptagent/execute` (a Folder child is re-queued to the scheduler).
//
// Cron parsing uses the `cron` crate (Quartz-style: sec min hour dom month dow
// year). Internal reads/writes use logic::object_exec_unchecked (the scheduler is
// a trusted process with no security principal); status changes are published so
// the web UI updates live.
//
// Inbound requests (from the API) are gated by an Auth0 M2M bearer token
// against this service's own "scheduler" audience (see common::auth0 and
// docs/auth0-m2m.md); if `~/.<namespace>.json` has no "scheduler" audience
// configured, Auth0 is treated as unconfigured and every request is allowed
// through unauthenticated (matching the .NET fallback for local development).
// Outbound dispatch to a ScriptAgent attaches an M2M bearer token the same
// way, via common::auth0::m2m_token("scriptagent").
// </auto-generated>
